[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Problem:** The cost estimate is presented as a flat "per panel-of-tests workload" range without clear decomposition by patient population size or lab panel breadth. The dominant cost driver is HealthLake storage (proportional to the longitudinal patient count and lab volume per patient) and SageMaker inference invocations (proportional to active-patient-times-monitored-LOINC-codes). A reader scoping a 100,000-patient health-system implementation versus a 5,000-patient specialty-clinic implementation needs to know which factors drive the cost variance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Fix:** Add to the cost estimate: "Per-workload cost scales with patient population size and lab panel breadth. The $300-$1,500/month range assumes a 10,000-50,000-patient cohort with 5-10 monitored LOINC codes (typical for a CKD-and-diabetes panel). A 100,000-patient health-system deployment with a broader panel (20-30 LOINC codes covering CKD, diabetes, anemia, liver, and electrolytes) can reach $2,500-$5,000/month, with HealthLake storage and SageMaker inference as the dominant cost drivers."
